text.tspan: Number of deaths from volcanic eruptions, World, 1570 to 2017
Deaths from volcanic eruption events includes direct deaths from volcanic eruptions, in addition to secondary impacts
(such as a tsunami or earthquake triggered by an eruption). Due to data availability, reporting and evidence, it's
expected that recent data will be more complete than the long historical record.
Source: National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC) of the NOAA
